<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="304" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,870,1617]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,870,896]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body moderately narrowly elongate; maxillary palpomere long, with elongate maxillary palpomere 2, about as long as apical palpomere; anterior portion of head between antennal insertion and anterior margin of eye moderately long, with distinct semicircular notch; pronotum with or without mediobasal impression; middle surface of each elytron with or without indistinct irregular elevations between punctures; meso- and metatibiae covered by dense and stout spines; apex of median lobe wide and deeply sinuate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,870,1617]" box="[199,834,1050,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,1050,1076]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Species included.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Erichson, 1840)" authorityName="Shavrin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Erichson" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[409,829,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Anthobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="algidum">
<emphasis box="[409,631,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Anthobium algidum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Erichson, W. F." box="[646,821,1051,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" pagination="401 - 954" refId="ref34311" refString="Erichson, W. F. (1840) Genera et species Staphylinorum insectorum coleopterorum familiae. (1). F. H. Morin, Berlin, pp. 401 - 954. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59644" type="book chapter" year="1840">Erichson, 1840</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="304" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,870,1617]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1087,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Remarks.</emphasis>
Regarding the general shape of the body and long elytra with indistinct irregular elevations between punctures in middle portions of each elytron, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shavrin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Erichson" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[680,806,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Anthobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="algidum">
<emphasis box="[680,697,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[714,806,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">algidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to some species (e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="Shavrin &amp; Smetana, 2017" authorityName="Shavrin &amp; Smetana" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Anthobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daliense">
<emphasis box="[1181,1198,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1215,1308,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">daliense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shavrin, A. V. &amp; Smetana, A." pageId="3" pageNumber="304" pagination="1 - 39" refId="ref36872" refString="Shavrin, A. V. &amp; Smetana, A. (2017) A revision of Eastern Palaearctic Anthobium Leach, 1819 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Omaliinae: Anthophagini). I. Gracilipalpe, morchella and nigrum groups. Zootaxa, 4365 (1), 1 - 39. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4365.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Shavrin &amp; Smetana, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) of the 
<emphasis box="[414,551,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">gracilipalpe</emphasis>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shavrin, A. V. &amp; Smetana, A." box="[641,936,1159,1185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" pagination="1 - 39" refId="ref36872" refString="Shavrin, A. V. &amp; Smetana, A. (2017) A revision of Eastern Palaearctic Anthobium Leach, 1819 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Omaliinae: Anthophagini). I. Gracilipalpe, morchella and nigrum groups. Zootaxa, 4365 (1), 1 - 39. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4365.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Shavrin &amp; Smetana 2017</bibRefCitation>
), from which it differs by the presence of a distinct notch between the antennal insertion and the anterior margin of the eye, the absence of fine crenulation on the lateral edges of the pronotum and the latero-apical margins of elytra, the absence of longitudinal elevations in the median portion of the elytra, and stouter setation of meso- and metatibia. Based on the presence of a similar notch in the latero-apical portions of the head, the absence of the crenulation on the lateral edges of the pronotum and elytra, and similar features of the setation of meso- and metatibia, it is similar to species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shavrin" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Paykull" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[1126,1201,1339,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Anthobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tectum">
<emphasis box="[1126,1201,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">tectum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, from which it can be distinguished by a larger and more elongate body, the shape of the apical portion of the head (more protruding apicad), and a less transverse pronotum, which is more narrowed posteriad than anteriad. From both groups, it differs by narrower apical portions of the mandibles, a narrower maxilla with markedly longer maxillary palpomeres 2, and a different morphology of the aedeagus, with a wide and deeply sinuate apical margin of the median lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,870,1617]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">
The shape of the median lobe (deeply sinuate apical margin) is similar to that in species of other genera of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1819" box="[151,274,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Anthobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Anthobium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group: western Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName authority="Reitter, 1909" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1909" box="[593,908,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Deliphrosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[593,752,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Deliphrosoma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter, E." box="[761,908,1555,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" pagination="41 - 80" refId="ref36385" refString="Reitter, E. (1909) Fauna Germanica. Die Kafer des Deutschen Reiche. Nach der analytischen Methode bearbeitet. II Band. Schriften des Deutschen Lehrervereins fur Naturkunde 24. K. G. Lutz, Stuttgart, 392 pp., pls. 41 - 80." type="book chapter" year="1909">Reitter, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zerche, L." box="[925,1071,1555,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" pagination="313 - 332" refId="ref37701" refString="Zerche, L. (1991) Beitrag zur Taxonomie und Verbreitung der Gattung Deliphrosoma Reitter, 1909 (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Omaliinae). Beitrage zur Entomologie, 41, 313 - 332." type="journal article" year="1991">Zerche 1991</bibRefCitation>
) and some species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Erichson, 1839" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[151,438,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,261,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">Arpedium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Erichson, W. F." box="[269,438,1591,1617]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" pagination="385 - 740" refId="ref34280" refString="Erichson, W. F. (1839) Die Kafer der Mark Brandenburg. Erster Band. Zweite Abtheilung. Morin, Berlin, pp. 385 - 740." type="book chapter" year="1839">Erichson, 1839</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. Nearctic 
<taxonomicName authority="Fauvel, 1878" authorityName="Fauvel" authorityYear="1878" box="[604,891,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Arpedium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schwarzi">
<emphasis box="[604,621,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[635,735,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="304">schwarzi</emphasis>
Fauvel, 1878
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Campbell, J. M." box="[944,1148,1591,1617]" pageId="3" pageNumber="304" pagination="487 - 527" refId="ref34041" refString="Campbell, J. M. (1984) A revision of the North American Omaliinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). The genera Arpedium Erichson and Eucnecosum Reitter. The Canadian Entomologist, 116, 487 - 527. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 116487 - 4" type="journal article" year="1984">Campbell (1984))</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
